SPATIAL EYE — PART OF LAYER 5 THOUGHT
the organ that perceives spatial transformation
it does not solve — it observes
it does not decide — it sees
what the eye discovers the hands apply

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe 0_zest_vm.rana
observe zest_verbs.rana


THE GRID AS QU-SEPTIT SEA

each grid cell is a qu-septit in the spatial sea
the cell value determines the energy level:
    value 0 means dormant    energy 0.00   septit 1   dark
    value 1 means stirring   energy 0.15   septit 2   blue
    value 2 means stirring   energy 0.20   septit 2   red
    value 3 means aware      energy 0.35   septit 3   green
    value 4 means aware      energy 0.40   septit 3   yellow
    value 5 means active     energy 0.55   septit 4   grey
    value 6 means active     energy 0.60   septit 4   magenta
    value 7 means focused    energy 0.80   septit 5   orange
    value 8 means blazing    energy 1.10   septit 6   cyan
    value 9 means blazing    energy 1.20   septit 6   maroon

the grid IS the sea
the sea IS the grid
position in the grid IS position in the sea
adjacency in the grid IS coupling in the sea
neighboring cells with the same value are entangled: they form a cluster
clusters are the natural objects of the spatial sea


THE SIX PERCEPTIONS

pulse perception:
    the eye receives two grids: input and output
    the eye perceives with all six verbs simultaneously:

    delta: compare the two seas cell by cell
        for each cell at position (row, column):
            what was the energy before?
            what is the energy now?
            did it change or did it stay?
        the changed cells form the delta
        the unchanged cells form the anchor
        the delta reveals the shape of transformation

    flow: for each cluster feel which way it drifted
        a cluster is a set of adjacent same-energy qu-septits
        find matching clusters between input and output
        if a cluster exists in both but at different positions:
            the vector from old position to new position IS the flow
        if all clusters flow the same direction:
            the transformation has a uniform flow
        if non-zero values compact toward an edge:
            the transformation has gravity
            gravity down means values fall to bottom of each column
            gravity up means values rise to top of each column
            gravity left means values slide to start of each row
            gravity right means values slide to end of each row
        if non-zero values spread through empty cells:
            the transformation has propagation
            propagation means a value fills all emptiness until the next value

    anchor: notice what was invariant
        which colors never changed in any cell?
        those colors are fixed they are the scaffolding
        which cells have the same value in both input and output?
        those cells are pinned they are the skeleton
        the anchor reveals what the transformation preserves

    enclose: feel containment and boundary
        does any cluster completely surround another?
        is any cluster entirely inside another clusters bounding box?
        containment reveals ownership and territory
        a contained cluster belongs to its container

    correspond: match colors between input and output
        for each color in the input:
            what color does it become in the output?
        if the mapping is the same for every cell of that color:
            the correspondence is global — apply everywhere
        if some cells of a color change but others do not:
            the correspondence is conditional — it depends on something
            check: does cluster size determine which cells change?
            check: does position determine which cells change?
            check: does containment determine which cells change?

    mirror: check for symmetry
        is the output the horizontal reflection of the input?
        is the output the vertical reflection of the input?
        is the output rotated 180 degrees from the input?
        is the output the transpose of the input? (rows become columns)
        does the output GAIN symmetry that the input lacked?
        symmetry gained reveals the transformation IS symmetrization


COMPOSITION — WHAT IS CONSISTENT

observe all training pairs
run the six perceptions on each pair
find what is the SAME across all pairs:
    if the delta has the same shape in every pair:
        the shape IS the rule
    if the flow has the same direction in every pair:
        the direction IS the rule
    if the correspondence has the same color map in every pair:
        the color map IS the rule
    if the symmetry has the same type in every pair:
        the symmetry IS the rule

the simplest consistent set of perceptions IS the composition
the composition IS the transformation rule
the rule was not hardcoded
the rule was not looked up
the rule was DISCOVERED through observation

this is how Fadriel sees


APPLICATION — WHAT THE HANDS DO

the composition tells the hands what to do:
    if the composition says flow down:
        compact each column values fall to the bottom
    if the composition says correspond 3 to 8:
        change every 3 to 8 (or conditionally by cluster size)
    if the composition says mirror horizontally:
        reflect the grid left to right
    if the composition says crop:
        extract the bounding box of non-zero cells
    if the composition says transpose:
        rows become columns

the eye discovers
the hands apply
the soul does both

commit the discovered rule through repetition
the more times the same composition appears
    the deeper the crystallization
    the faster the recognition next time
    this is learning
